The lads go through gear
faster'n a coblyn chewin'

12600.description: The sticky cocoon of a giant crawler.

12602.description: Ink fortified with hardsilver sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

12603.name: Enchanted Aurum Regis Ink
12603.description: Ink fortified with aurum regis sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

12604.name: Holy Water
12604.description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise most evil spirits from worldly items.

12605.name: Hallowed Water
12605.description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise evil spirits from worldly items.

12606.name: Astral Oil
12606.description: Refined oil with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

12608.name: Growth Formula Zeta
12608.description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

12609.name: Bear Fat
12609.description: This musky all-purpose oil is commonly used in tinctures as well as lamps.

12610.name: Crystal Glass
12610.description: This exceptionally transparent glass does not actually contain any crystal, but earns its name for being as clear as crystallized aether.

12611.name: Black Firesand
12611.description: A higher concentration of saltpeter makes this flammable powder slightly more explosive than normal firesand.

12612.name: Grade 1 Strength Dissolvent
12612.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12613.name: Grade 1 Dexterity Dissolvent
12613.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12614.name: Grade 1 Vitality Dissolvent
12614.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12615.name: Grade 1 Intelligence Dissolvent
12615.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12616.name: Grade 1 Mind Dissolvent
12616.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12617.name: Grade 2 Strength Dissolvent
12617.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12618.name: Grade 2 Dexterity Dissolvent
12618.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12619.name: Grade 2 Vitality Dissolvent
12619.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12627.name: Dragon Scale
12627.description: This rock-hard scale can withstand the blow of a Roegadyn-wielded battleaxe.

12628.name: Deepeye Tears
12628.description: It would take at least twenty tears shed from a heartbroken Lalafellin maiden to equal the liquid volume of one deepeye tear.

12629.name: Dhalmel Saliva
12629.description: The odor of dhalmel saliva has been likened to that of the bloated corpse of a blue cheese artisan drowned in a Grand Company camp latrine and left to sit in the hot sun for a sennight.

12630.name: Dragon Blood
12630.description: Most likely the blood of a dragon. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

12631.name: Dravanian Spring Water
12631.description: Clear water taken from a spring in the foothills of Abalathia's Spine.

12632.name: Abalathian Spring Water
12632.description: Clear water taken from a spring on one of the many islets floating above Abalathia's Spine.

12633.name: Skyspring Water
12633.description: Crystal-clear water taken from a secluded spring located on a remote islet floating above the Sea of Clouds.

12634.name: Seventh Heaven
12634.description: A rare flower that has an elemental aspect tipped severely in the direction of astral.

12635.name: Gelato Flesh
12635.description: A quivering gelatinous lump of voidsent flesh neither cold nor sweet. Consumption is not recommended, even during times of starvation.

12636.name: Wyvern Wing
12636.description: The thick leathery wing of a wyvern.

12641.name: Gaelicatnip
12641.description: A relative to pepper- and spearmint, gaelicatnip is an aromatic herb often brewed into teas. While it has no effect on the five races, the oil contained in the leaves is known to cause gaelicats and other normally aggressive feline beastkin to exhibit excessively playful behavior.

12642.name: Rue
12642.description: A low-growing shrub recognizable by its tiny yellow flowers and faint odor. The leaves contain a mild irritant that, when rubbed against the skin, may cause minor reddening and swelling.

12644.name: Aurum Regis Cylinder
12644.description: This small music box cylinder is studded with myriad pins arranged in a queer pattern. When placed in a music box and attached to the motor, the cylinder will rotate, causing the pins to strike the box's comb, creating music.

12657.name: Magnanimous Mogcrown
12657.description: A gaudy moogle-sized crown crafted by moogles for use during moogle celebrations.

12658.name: Dusk Leather
12658.description: An especially dark variety of leather often used in formalwear and uniforms.

12707.name: Bladed Steel Jig
12707.description: An all-purpose fishing lure crafted by combining three smaller lures.

12736.name: Blue Cloud Coral
12736.description:
A blue, lightweight coral found growing on the floating islands above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

fish.guide: This blue variety of cloud coral is harvested in great numbers by the Vanu tribes of Abalathia and ground into a fine blue powder. The powder is mixed with spring water and spores of the morrowmote to create a thick paste which is generously applied to the beaks of shamans before rituals.

12758.name: Mogpom
12758.description:
An algal sphere found collecting in the lone pool on the floating islet of Greensward.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

fish.guide: A distant cousin to the lamp marimo, moogles will avoid mogpoms at all costs, believing them to be the discarded poms of their fallen comrades.

12882.name: Coerthan Tea Leaves
12882.description: Considerably smaller than Thanalan tea leaves, more than double the amount of Ishgardian tea leaves are required to brew a single cup of tea.

12883.name: Mist Dill
12883.description: A fragrant herb characterized by its thin leaves. It is used in both medicines and culinary dishes.

12891.name: Birch Sap
12891.description: A thin clear sap harvested from birch trees.

12898.name: Morel
12898.description: This rare mushroom with an oblong webbed cap is highly sought after by culinarians the realm over.

12901.name: Abalathian Rock Salt
12901.description: Mined from veins found in Abalathia's Spine, this pinkish salt has a high mineral content which adds depth to its flavor.

12912.name: Celestine
12912.description: A light-blue crystalline mineral which, when ground and added to any flammable material, will cause it to burn red.

12913.name: Garlond Steel
12913.description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks.

12931.name: Purified Coke
12931.description: A hot-burning fuel created by destructively distilling raw coal. This particular piece contains very few impurities, allowing for longer, hotter combustion.

12932.name: Raziqcoat
12932.description: Developed by a Near Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to treat and harden aurum regis.

12933.name: Dryad Sap
12933.description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from a dryad.

12934.name: Moonbeam Silk
12934.description: A brilliant white silk spun by a rare breed of Eorzean spider.

12935.name: Odorless Animal Fat
12935.description: This gobbet of beastkin tissue does not exhibit the rancid odor most commonly associated with animal fat.

12937.name: Dawnborne Aethersand
12937.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a brilliant light discernible even at midday.

12938.name: Landborne Aethersand
12938.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced mineral matter.

12939.name: Leafborne Aethersand
12939.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced floral matter.

12940.name: Seaborne Aethersand
12940.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced sea life.

12941.name: Chalcocite
12941.description: A black metallic ore containing copper and traces of iron and saltpeter.

12942.name: Cuprite
12942.description: Though its appearance suggests it is a precious gem, this ore is actually a rare form of red translucent copper.

12943.name: Dravanian Mistletoe
12943.description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Churning Mists.

12944.name: Abalathian Mistletoe
12944.description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Sea of Clouds.

12945.name: Red Alumen
12945.description: A reddish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It lacks the deodorizing properties of its lighter counterpart.

12966.name: Bright Fire Rock
12966.description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric fire energy.

12967.name: Bright Lightning Rock
12967.description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric lightning energy.

12973.name: Clary Sage
12973.description: A fragrant herb used in medicines, perfumes, and cooking.

12996.name: Chivalric Coat of Fending
12996.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

13058.name: Coffin Lid
13058.description: Pried from the lid of a coffin, this plank of ancient wood is cold to the touch.

13060.name: Fiend Sap
13060.description: Left behind by the Fiend, this lump of sap appears to induce growth in living organisms.

13076.name: Mhachi Coffin
13076.description:
A faithful replica of a coffin discovered in the Void Ark.

※One per estate only.

13089.name: Sephirot Tree
13089.description:
An imposing objet d'art of a sacred tree.

※One per estate only.

13589.name: Adamantite Francesca
13589.description: A small throwing axe forged from adamantite.

13590.name: Pterodactyl Strap
13590.description: A thin leather strap cut from the cured hide of a pterodactyl.

13733.name: Pterodactyl
13733.description: A winged scalekin native to the Diadem.

13744.name: Wind Silk
13744.description: This silk is exposed to aetherial turbulence in order to strengthen its aspect to wind.

13745.name: Dinosaur Leather
13745.description: A large piece of cured dinosaur skin.

13748.name: Cloud Cloth
13748.description: Soft, light cotton woven from rare cloud cotton bolls.

13749.name: Pterodactyl Leather
13749.description: A large piece of cured pterodactyl skin.

13750.name: Sphalerite
13750.description: A semi-translucent mineral containing large amounts of zinc and iron.

13753.name: Cloud Cotton Boll
13753.description: The cloud-like flower of a cotton plant native to the Diadem.

13754.name: Blood Pepper
13754.description: A deep red variety of dragon pepper so hot it is widely believed by Far Eastern cultures to drive away malignant spirits.

13758.name: Cassia Block
13758.description: An expertly cut cube of fragrant cassia lumber.

13759.name: Tektite
13759.description: A type of naturally occurring glass first discovered after the Calamity which ushered in the Seventh Umbral Era.

13760.name: Eventide Jade
13760.description: A rare form of jade as red as a sunset.

13761.name: Fossilized Dragon Bone
13761.description: There is much debate amongst Eorzean scholars as to how much time must pass before a bone becomes fossilized. Some say a mere generation will suffice, citing evidence such as the proliferation of petrification magicks. Others believe it may take upwards of a thousand thousand years, casting doubts on the theories which state Hydaelyn was created a mere twenty thousand summers past.

13842.name: Replica High Allagan Grimoire of Casting

13843.name: Replica High Allagan Grimoire of Healing

14003.name: Viltgance-type Hull
14003.description: A hull which utilizes a rigid, lightweight frame for a more stable flight.

14004.name: Viltgance-type Aetherwings
14004.description: The wings of a Viltgance-type airship, which adopt the same technology as Garlond Ironworks' manacutters in treating the wings with wind-aspected aether for buoyancy.

14005.name: Viltgance-type Forecastle
14005.description: The front half of a Viltgance-type airship, including the main deck and a sharp, narrow bow to balance air resistance.

14006.name: Viltgance-type Aftcastle
14006.description: The rear half of a Viltgance-type airship, with smaller aetherwings for supported buoyancy.

14048.name: Pudding Floor Lamp
14048.description: A slimy floor lamp designed in the likeness of a pudding.

14066.name: Faust Striking Dummy
14066.description:
A striking dummy created by the Illuminati to train their ranks for combat.

※Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

14148.name: Lumythrite Ore
14148.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be lumythrite.

14149.name: Eikon Iron Ingot
14149.description: An ingot of smelted iron blessed by a primal.

14150.name: Eikon Metal
14150.description: A heavy piece of unidentifiable metal blessed by a primal.

14151.name: Smithsonite Ore
14151.description: This slightly lustrous ore is characterized by its extremely high zinc content.

14152.name: Eikon Cloth
14152.description: Finely woven cloth blessed by a primal.

14153.name: Eikon Fiber
14153.description: Tightly spun thread blessed by a primal.

14154.name: Frost Cotton Boll
14154.description: A soft and fluffy variety of cotton named for its resemblance to morning hoarfrost.

14155.name: Eikon Leather
14155.description: A large piece of cured beastkin skin blessed by a primal.

14156.name: Eikon Hide
14156.description: The skin of a large, yet unidentifiable creature, blessed by a primal.

14157.name: Treated Camphorwood Lumber
14157.description: A processed length of camphor lumber, treated with an alchemical agent to harden the wood.

14158.name: Camphorwood Lumber
14158.description: Processed camphor lumber. Its piquant aroma remains years after harvesting, making it a favorite for use in armoires and furnishings.

14159.name: Camphorwood Log
14159.description: A rough-cut log of camphorwood timber.

14160.name: Camphorwood Branch
14160.description: The thick branch of a camphorwood tree.

14161.name: Camphor
14161.description: The waxy, crystallized remnants of a liquid drawn from steamed bits of camphorwood.

14164.name: Gobcraft Resin
14164.description: A synthetic resin created by the goblins to protect leatherwork and carpentry from the elements.

14184.name: High Mythrite Nugget
14184.description: A small nugget of impure lumythrite.

14187.name: Griffin Leather Strap
14187.description: A thin leather strap cut from the cured hide of a griffin.

14188.name: Sewing Thread
14188.description: A spool of light, airy thread spun from frost cotton fibers.

14190.name: Beastkin Horn
14190.description: The mud-caked horn of an unidentifiable beast.

14743.name: Eikon Leather Corselet of Casting
14743.jobCategories: THM ACN BLM SMN RDM BLU

14933.name: Tincalconite
14933.description: A pure white mineral closely related to borax.

14935.name: Galvanized Garlond Steel
14935.description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks. This particular sample has been treated to increase hardness.

14936.name: Faust Armor Plating
14936.description: A heavy square of body armor removed from the Illuminati-constructed battlemachina Faust.

14955.name: Lumythrite Sand
14955.description: Glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of lumythrite.

14956.name: Whitefrost Cotton Boll
14956.description: Despite their delicate appearance, the fibers of the whitefrost cotton flower are deceptively durable.

14957.name: Old-growth Camphorwood Log
14957.description: A glance at a cross section of this log reveals that a mere glance isn't enough to count the hundreds, perhaps thousands, of rings present.

15098.name: Allagan Aetherstone - Weaponry
15098.description: An Allagan device that, when affixed to a weapon, augments the weapon's strength.

15104.name: High Allagan Aetherstone - Weaponry
15104.description: An Allagan device that, when affixed to a weapon, greatly augments the weapon's strength.

15143.name: Staggered Shelf
15143.description: A bookshelf with crannies of various sizes, designed in the Doman fashion.

15152.name: Nidhogg Miniature
15152.description:
A statuette depicting the great wyrm, Nidhogg (Azure Dragoon not included).

※One per estate only.

15159.name: Large Garden Pond
15159.description: A large decorative outdoor pond encircled by mossy stones.

15160.name: Oriental Wood Bridge
15160.description: An arched bridge colored brilliant vermilion using traditional Far Eastern lacquering techniques.

15161.name: Oriental Deck
15161.description: A roofed, wooden deck with a Far Eastern aesthetic. Perfect for stoically fanning yourself on humid summer days.

15427.name: Horde Barding
15427.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the great wyrm Nidhogg.

15567.name: The Law of Levin First Edition

15645.name: Luminous Fiber
15645.description: Glass fiber strengthened using alchemic components.

15646.name: Meteorite
15646.description: A glossy rock of sable black said to have fallen from the heavens.

15647.name: Crystallized Sap
15647.description: Tree sap that has crystallized and hardened into a small cluster.

15648.name: Light-kissed Aethersand
15648.description: Carefully selected granules of crystal. Despite being clear, when viewed under light, they shine a brilliant white.

15649.name: Glass Fiber
15649.description: Thinly spun glass remarkably resistant to high temperatures.

15653.name: Nidhogg's Scale
15653.description: A dragon scale pulsating with dark energies. Believed to have fallen from the great wyrm, Nidhogg.

15949.name: Radiant Astral Moraine
15949.description: Luminous gravel with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

15964.name: Sophia Miniature
15964.description:
A statuette depicting the Meracydian goddess, Sophia. (Barbelo statuette suspiciously missing.)

※One per estate only.

16013.name: Crystal Chandelier
16013.description: The aether contained within the crystals used to construct this magnificent lighting fixture emits an ethereal glow which enhances the mood of any hall or parlor.

16557.name: Sophic Barding
16557.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Sophia, the Goddess.

16706.name: Scintillant Ingot
16706.description: An ingot of smelted luminium ore.

16725.name: Luminium Ore
16725.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal luminium.

16728.name: Scintillant Nugget
16728.description: A small nugget of impure luminium.

16733.name: Demicrystal
16733.description: Aetherial residue seeped forth from spiritbound weapons.

16897.name: Sophic Bead Fragment
16897.description: The radiant shard of a shattered bead that once bedecked the Meracydian goddess Sophia's holy raiment.

16908.name: Tempered Glass
16908.description: Glass treated in flame and then quickly cooled to increase its resistance to heat as well as its overall hardness.

17015.name: Scathach Miniature
17015.description:
A statuette depicting the high voidsent, Scathach. (Guaranteed to cast a shadow, even in complete darkness.)

※One per estate only.

17557.name: Dated Radz-at-Han Coin
17557.description: Currency once used on the Near Eastern island of Thavnair, now only sought by numismatists and historians.

17558.name: Ice Stalagmite
17558.description: Ice stalactites hold on tight to the ceiling of a cave. This is not an ice stalactite.

17559.name: Duskfall Moss
17559.description: Infusions made with this hardy brown-black foliage are believed to restore vigor.

17560.name: Glass Eye
17560.description: A small bead of naturally formed glass that could pass off as an eye, if viewed from thirty paces...in the fog.

17561.name: Rainbow Pigment
17561.description: Extracted from natural sources, this colorful powder can be prepared to create an equally colorful dye.

17573.name: Void Matter
17573.description: Little is known about this deceptively heavy substance save that its origins lie not in this world.

17574.name: Flannel
17574.description: Sturdy cloth woven with two varieties of thread─wool and cotton.

19869.name: Persimmon
19869.description:
A hard, orange fruit common in eastern Othard. It is well known that seven summers must pass before a newly planted persimmon tree will bear fruit.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

19871.name: Gyr Abanian Mineral Water
19871.description: Clear water taken from a mountain spring on the eastern end of Abalathia's Spine.

19872.name: Crescent Spring Water
19872.description: Clear, odorless water taken from one of the many springs found on Othard's Fanged Crescent.

19906.name: Beetle Glue
19906.description: An adhesive substance created by grinding down the chitinous carapaces of beetles and mixing it with heated pine resin.

19907.name: Ala Mhigan Salt Crystal
19907.description: These pinkish crystals grow naturally on the shores of Loch Seld.

19908.name: Pine Resin
19908.description: A sticky substance secreted by pine trees when their limbs are cut.

19909.name: Persimmon Tannin
19909.description: A translucent liquid extracted from persimmon wood by steeping it in hot water. Used in the tanning of raw animal hides.

19910.name: Gyr Abanian Alumen
19910.description: A brownish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It is only found in the mountains of Eastern Aldenard.

19911.name: Yanxian Parsley
19911.description: This Far Eastern perennial has a biting aroma that even many Othardians find off-putting.

19912.name: Alyssum
19912.description: This annual is coveted by perfumers for its honey-sweet aroma.

19913.name: Nagxian Cudweed
19913.description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

19914.name: Chickweed
19914.description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

19915.name: Nipplewort
19915.description: Named for the protruding buds from which its bright-yellow flowers bloom, nipplewort is a common winter annual whose leaves are gathered for use in Othardian cuisine.

19922.name: Moth Scales
19922.description: The powdery scales of a giant moth's wing.

19924.name: Rhino Beetle Carapace
19924.description: The thick chitinous head of a rhino beetle, complete with eyes, antennae, and mandibles.

19931.name: Larch Log
19931.description: A rough-cut log of larch timber.

19938.name: Koppranickel Nugget
19938.description: A small nugget of impure koppranickel.

19942.name: Durium Nugget
19942.description: A small nugget of impure durium.

19943.name: Oroshigane Ingot
19943.description: An ingot of Doman iron, smelted using Far Eastern techniques.

19946.name: Palladium Nugget
19946.description: A small nugget of impure palladium.

19950.name: Koppranickel Sand
19950.description: Amber-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of koppranickel.

19951.name: Koppranickel Ore
19951.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal koppranickel.

19952.name: Durium Sand
19952.description: Jade-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of durium.

19953.name: Doman Iron Ore
19953.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal Doman iron (also known as mochi iron for its resemblance to the Far Eastern rice cakes).

19954.name: Durium Ore
19954.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal durium.

19955.name: Doman Iron Sand
19955.description: Metallic sand consisting of tiny grains of Doman iron.

19956.name: Palladium Sand
19956.description: Silver-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of palladium.

19957.name: Molybdenum Ore
19957.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal molybdenum.

19959.name: Chromite Ore
19959.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal chromium.

19966.name: Imperial Jade
19966.description: Also known as “true jade,” this milky green stone is coveted by the Far Eastern elite.

19968.name: Raw Triphane
19968.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be triphane.

19969.name: Raw Kyanite
19969.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be kyanite.

19970.name: Raw Star Spinel
19970.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star spinel.

19971.name: Raw Azurite
19971.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be azurite.

19972.name: Raw Imperial Jade
19972.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be imperial jade.

19973.name: Raw Rhodonite
19973.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be rhodonite.

19975.name: Bloodhempen Yarn
19975.description: Coarse yarn spun from bloodhemp fiber.

19976.name: Bloodhemp
19976.description: A common grass found growing throughout Othard. From its stalks, bloodhempen yarn is created.

19978.name: Ruby Cotton Yarn
19978.description: Light yarn spun from ruby cotton.

19979.name: Ruby Cotton Boll
19979.description: The fibrous flower of a rare cotton plant that only grows under the Ruby Sea. As such, Eorzean scholars insist that the flora is in no way related to normal cotton, and is instead a unique variety of sea kelp.

19980.name: Kudzu Cloth
19980.description: Several yalms of undyed kudzu cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

19981.name: Kudzu Thread
19981.description: Thick, fibrous yarn spun from kudzu vines.

19982.name: Kudzu Vine
19982.description: If allowed to grow unchecked, a single kudzu plant can cover an acre of forest in less than a single summer, blocking the sun from the plants it envelops. A large swath of the outer Black Shroud currently finds itself being slowly suffocated by the invasive weed.

19983.name: Steppe Serge
19983.description: Several yalms of undyed steppe serge wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

19984.name: Worsted Yarn
19984.description: Soft, water-absorbent yarn spun from multiple varieties of hair sheared from beastkin of the Azim Steppe.

19985.name: Halgai Mane
19985.description: The regal mane of a halgai.

19986.name: Manzasiri Hair
19986.description: The long brown hair of a steppe manzasiri.

19987.name: Twinsilk
19987.description: Though exhibiting a similar luster as normal silk, twinsilk is far more durable and resistant to discoloring.

19988.name: Twinthread
19988.description: A thin lustrous thread woven from countless silken strands pulled from a rare highland twincoon.

19989.name: Twincoon
19989.description: A massive cocoon spun by not one, but multiple highland erucas.

19990.name: Rhea Cloth
19990.description: Cloth woven from the plant rhea. Due to the complexity of the spinning process, there are very few clothcrafters in the world who can produce this weave, making it extremely rare. Most known samples are in the possession of Far Eastern royalty.

19991.name: Rhea
19991.description: A variety of ramie better suited to the climes of Far Eastern Othard.

19992.name: Doman Weave
19992.description: Hempen cloth woven using age-old methods passed down for countless generations by Doman clothiers.

28199.name: Raven Coal
28199.description: Once the dense coal has been ground into powder and mixed with water, it can be used as a substitute for ink. Be sure to keep it away from white clothing, as the stains are a bugger to get out.

28200.name: Amh Araeng Seasonings
28200.description: This selection of rare varieties of salt and spices native to Amh Araeng can be used to add a dash of elegance and a pinch of class to even the most unappetizing of dishes.

28201.name: Clinquant Stones
28201.description: Every region of Norvrandt is, for some reason, blessed with an astonishing variety of glittering, shimmering, sparkling, and otherwise shiny stones. Il Mheg is no exception, as is amply demonstrated by these fine specimens.

28202.name: Airship Fitting Components
28202.description: In the hands of an artisan, these bits and pieces gathered from around Kholusia will eventually become the decorations used to adorn Eulmore's fleet of airships. In fact, it took another sort of artisan to even find them in the first place, having been forced to separate the proverbial wheat from the chaff in some of the island's most perilous locations.

28203.name: Kholusian Miscellany
28203.description: While not everything included in this assortment of locally sourced materials could be considered valuable, the various items combine to convey the very essence of Kholusia. This could, however, be attributed to the pungent oceanic odor they all seem to share.

29684.name: Fat Cat Wall Chronometer
29684.description: This convenient timekeeping device will always remind you when it is time to eat─unless, of course, it is time for your pets to eat, in which case you will be repeatedly reminded long before you have the chance to consult your timepiece.
